1
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,640
Hey, you're going there to preserve fish

2
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,160
or looking for something else?

3
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,920
Is there something to look for?

4
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,400
Don't go. Don't go!

5
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,520
Look ahead.

6
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,560
Don't turn around.

7
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,720
The moment you look back, you die!

8
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,160
Die!

9
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,760
I really saw it.

10
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:10,120
It wasn't a rock
but I'm not sure it was coral either.

11
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:11,960
Coral?

12
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,280
Someone once told me

13
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,600
this area is cursed.

14
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,280
No one can stop a storm,

15
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:16,680
especially the storm inside the heart
of someone driven by vengeance.

16
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,640
Thank you.

17
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,360
Kaimook,

18
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,200
what happened?

19
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,000
I don't know.

20
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,800
The underwater current
suddenly got really strong.

21
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:41,640
Yes.

22
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,840
That was strange.

23
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,080
What?

24
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,400
What's wrong?

25
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,640
Nothing.

26
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:36,720
I must've imagined it.

27
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,720
Then please excuse me.

28
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,320
Narathon.

29
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,040
Mr. Thon.

30
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,120
Mr. Thon.

31
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,080
How is it, buddy?

32
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:16,040
I still can't stop
thinking about that current.

33
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,680
It was really strange.

34
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,560
I've never seen anything like this before.

35
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:27,560
Don't tell me you're planning
to dive back down there again.

36
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,680
Yes.

37
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:35,440
I'm definitely going back down there.
But not today.

38
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:39,559
We're almost at the shore.
Should we go pack up our things?

39
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,679
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

40
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:42,919
Let me help.

41
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,400
Mr. Thon.

42
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,000
Mr. Thon.

43
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,720
What are you doing?

44
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,040
I…

45
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,600
I…

46
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,000
Are you okay, Kaimook?

47
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,240
Mook, are you alright?

48
00:10:57,280 --> 00:11:00,000
I'm fine now.
It was probably just seasick.

49
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,480
I think you came up
from the water too fast.

50
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,840
Let me take you to a doctor.

51
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,960
I'd rather go home and rest.

52
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,280
Mook,

53
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,720
are you sure it's nothing

54
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:15,960
more than seasickness?

55
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,680
Yes.

56
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,480
I was gonna ask earlier.
What exactly happened down there?

57
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,360
The current was too strong.

58
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,760
I couldn't fight against it.

59
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,640
What's wrong?

60
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,320
Nothing.

61
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:02,960
My child.

62
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,120
My child.

63
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:11,160
My house. My house!

64
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,880
My child!

65
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,080
My child!

66
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,320
My child.

67
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:41,920
My child.

68
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,760
Where's my child?

69
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,000
My child.

70
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,560
My child!

71
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:53,280
My child!

72
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,240
Who took my child?

73
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,400
Who took my child?!

74
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:09,320
So you think I don't know
how to use a camera

75
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:11,880
just like your student said?

76
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,080
No, no.

77
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,840
But underwater, maybe you didn't
press the shutter properly,

78
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:21,960
or something went wrong.

79
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,320
Hey,

80
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:27,000
you said yourself
you photographed the black coral,

81
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,920
but what is this?

82
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,720
Not a single image can be opened.

83
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,760
Hey, I didn't say

84
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,520
you were lying about the coral,

85
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:47,400
but these kinds of devices
can malfunction too.

86
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,720
But the angle you shot from

87
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,880
was the same angle I used.

88
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:58,160
So why isn't there even a trace
of the black coral in your pictures?

89
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:04,079
When I was taking pictures,
I was farther away than you.

90
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:06,200
And the water there was murky.

91
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,000
So what now?

92
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:16,040
Send the camera in
for another replacement?

93
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:20,440
Of course. It's genuinely defective,

94
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:22,680
I can be your witness.

95
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,640
You think the owner's gonna curse us out?

96
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:28,359
We've already gone through two cameras

97
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,920
and neither works.

98
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,000
I guess.

99
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:54,560
How have you been, Venerable Sir?

100
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,880
As you can see.

101
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,680
Did you come here for a visit?

102
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,040
Yes.

103
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,880
My daughter just graduated,

104
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:05,280
so I brought her here for a trip
before she starts her internship.

105
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:08,520
And I stopped by to let you know

106
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:12,280
that this year, I'd like to sponsor
the robe offering again.

107
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:14,440
Good, good.

108
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,080
- May you rejoice in this merit.
- Yes.

109
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:21,720
I'll have the temple steward
take care of it.

110
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,240
Thank you.

111
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,440
Oh, Venerable Sir.

112
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,600
You have a guest?

113
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:32,760
Oh. It's alright. Come in.

114
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,080
Please.

115
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:50,280
Prachaya's going back to Bangkok,
so I brought him to say goodbye to you.

116
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,240
Oh.

117
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,760
Well, Mek,

118
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:57,960
this is Mr. Narathon

119
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:00,600
and Professor Prachaya.

120
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:02,960
- Hello.
- Hello.

121
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:08,960
Professor Prachaya teaches photography

122
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:11,680
at the university in Bangkok.

123
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:16,240
My daughter talked about
someone named Professor Prachaya before.

124
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,680
He also teaches photography.
I'm not sure if that's you.

125
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,800
Really? What's your daughter's name?

126
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:21,920
It's Kaimook.

127
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,320
She's my student.

128
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,440
Oh, really?

129
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:31,160
Well then,

130
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:34,440
you're all acquainted already. Good.

131
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:38,440
And what do you do, Mr. Narathon?

132
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:42,480
I currently manage a fish farm.

133
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,320
Well,

134
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:47,120
rare sea fish and marine creatures.

135
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,920
They preserve them there.

136
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,200
That sounds very interesting.

137
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:55,080
If I get the chance,
I'd love to visit sometime.

138
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,320
Of course.

139
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,680
Do you already have plans for tonight?

140
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:03,560
Would you like to have dinner at my house?
We can also talk about marine life.

141
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,680
Well, I have to head back to Bangkok.

142
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,080
I can come.

143
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,880
But let me send my friend off first.

144
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,680
Of course. No problem.

145
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:15,800
Alright.

146
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,360
Then please excuse me, Venerable Sir.

147
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,320
Alright.

148
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,000
Goodbye, Mr. Mek.

149
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,600
- Goodbye.
- See you.

150
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:34,800
Good luck.

151
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,840
I'm really glad we met.

152
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:42,440
If I hadn't stopped by today,

153
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:45,000
I probably never
would've met Mr. Narathon.

154
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,720
What a coincidence.

155
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:51,800
Everything is already destined,

156
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,280
whether people are meant to meet

157
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,760
or drift apart.

158
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:03,520
In this world,
there is no such thing as coincidence.

159
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:15,560
Oh. You're actually going
all the way to Kaimook's house?

160
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:17,560
I thought you said you didn't like her.

161
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:21,680
Mr. Mek invited me personally.

162
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:23,400
How could I refuse? That'd be rude.

163
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,720
Someone like Mr. Narathon

164
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,840
is not that straightforward.

165
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:32,040
Are you planning
to do anything to my student?

166
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,880
You'll find out.

167
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:36,320
Hey, don't mess around.

168
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,520
Kaimook's a good kid.

169
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,280
I'm kidding.

170
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:44,400
Who would do anything
to your student? She's a badass.

171
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:47,480
Here, Professor.

172
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,400
Please take the camera in
for another replacement.

173
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,280
Let me know what the owner says.

174
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,440
Alright.

175
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:58,760
Okay, my friend.

176
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:02,120
By the way,

177
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,800
enjoy your dinner.

178
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:06,760
I'm going. Bye.

179
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,760
- Drive safe.
- Sure.

180
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,640
Whoa.

181
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,760
What is this?!

182
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:01,800
Help me!

183
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,960
Help me!

184
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:33,640
Da?

185
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,520
Da?

186
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,440
Da, what's wrong?!

187
00:25:56,240 --> 00:26:01,280
I saw… It must have been a ghost.

188
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,760
This house was just built a few years ago.

189
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,760
There's no ghost here.

190
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:12,120
You have to believe me. I didn't lie.

191
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,920
I really saw a ghost.

192
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,800
Are you sure you didn't imagine things?

193
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:58,800
My child…

194
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,000
My child.

195
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,080
Kang.

196
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,640
Thank you for saving me.

197
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:40,960
Kang.

198
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:57,120
Venerable Sir, did you see a woman?

199
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:00,720
I was drowning,

200
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:03,800
and a long-haired woman saved me.

201
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:07,160
But suddenly she disappeared.

202
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,920
I didn't even get to thank her.

203
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,000
Let's go back to the temple now.

204
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,720
Yes.

205
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,160
Let's stay in our own places.

206
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,640
Not harm one another.

207
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:22,800
Wait, Dara. Calm down.

208
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:25,120
This house is haunted.

209
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,760
Then why doesn't the ghost
haunt anyone else?

210
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,240
Why only you?

211
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:33,480
It's not even your house.

212
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,040
My dad, my mom, Na,

213
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:39,280
and I should be the ones
getting haunted more than anyone.

214
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,760
Kaimook, do you remember

215
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:44,000
when we went on that volunteer camp
before graduation?

216
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,720
And we stayed at that temple?

217
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:52,040
At that temple,
you saw a ghost at the pavilion

218
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,480
and couldn't sleep all night.

219
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:56,120
Even though no one else saw anything.

220
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:59,800
And what did the monk there say?

221
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:05,120
He said you could sense spirits.

222
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:09,160
And that's exactly why the ghost
doesn't haunt the rest of you.

223
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,520
- But--
- I don't care.

224
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:13,200
No matter what, I'm leaving.

225
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:20,200
Da, what happened?

226
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:23,120
Na, I'm going back to Bangkok.

227
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,440
There's a ghost here.

228
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,920
There's no ghost in this house.

229
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,120
You'll never understand how terrifying
it is unless you experience it yourself.

230
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:35,280
Huh? Well,

231
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:37,920
do you think I'm lying about the ghost?

232
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,520
No, Da.

233
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,520
I'm just saying

234
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:45,080
no one in this house
has ever seen a ghost before.

235
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,400
Except me, right?

236
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,360
I'm the only one who saw it clearly.

237
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:52,320
Alright.
If you don't believe me, it's fine.

238
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:54,240
I'm going back anyway.

239
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:57,320
Please call me a ride. I'm leaving.

240
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:09,440
How did Da see something like that?

241
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,440
What's this family meeting about?

242
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:16,000
This is Mr. Narathon.

243
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:19,240
This is my wife, Mhai.
And they are my son and daughter,

244
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,680
Mana and Kaimook.

245
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,480
- Hello.
- Hello.

246
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:27,760
Glad to see you again.

247
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:29,840
Likewise.

248
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,920
You already met each other?

249
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:34,160
Yes, Dad.

250
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:38,040
During the diving trip,
Mr. Narathon even saved Mook.

251
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:43,880
Saved? Does that mean Mook almost drowned?

252
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:47,200
Goodness, why didn't you tell me?

253
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:50,480
I didn't almost drown, Mom.
It was just a small accident.

254
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,800
So we're all acquainted already.

255
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:55,760
Good. Mr. Narathon
won't feel uncomfortable then.

256
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:58,360
Please make a few more dishes.

257
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:00,360
Sure, I'll handle it.

258
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:01,680
Okay.

259
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:04,320
In that case, I'll go freshen up.

260
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,560
Maybe you can show him the fish ponds.

261
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,360
Mook,

262
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:15,840
take care of Mr. Narathon for now.
I need to go check on Dara first.

263
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,239
Please excuse me for a moment.

264
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,719
Of course. Please feel free.

265
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,760
You still don't look fully recovered.

266
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:34,280
I'm fine now.

267
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:36,679
Thank you very much for helping me.

268
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,080
What are you laughing at?

269
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:45,800
I thought I'd never get to hear
you say thank you.

270
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:50,719
You probably think I'm rude, don't you?

271
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:55,920
Actually,
I care quite a lot about manners.

272
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,760
But with certain annoying people,

273
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:01,280
I don't think it's always necessary.

274
00:35:03,120 --> 00:35:05,840
What? How am I annoying?

275
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:07,600
If I'm annoying,

276
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:09,560
your father and brother

277
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:12,200
wouldn't have asked you
to take care of me.

278
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,920
Well,

279
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,480
I'm about to take you
to see the fish ponds.

280
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:18,960
Follow me.

281
00:35:58,480 --> 00:36:00,000
Mr. Narathon.

282
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,560
Hey, that…

283
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:23,200
Hey. Hey.

284
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:30,760
Hey, tour guide. Aren't you going to
explain anything to me?

285
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:33,160
What would you like to know?

286
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:37,480
I don't know anything now.

287
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,160
Should I believe that?

288
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,760
You graduated in marine science,
didn't you?

289
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,360
Did you look into my background?

290
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,360
I Googled you.

291
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:52,000
I just typed in your name

292
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:53,880
and your whole history popped right up.

293
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:56,800
Why were you looking me up?

294
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,840
I just wanted to know

295
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,400
who you are.

296
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:05,760
More importantly,

297
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:10,120
whether you're smart enough
to use that underwater camera model.

298
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:19,640
So after reading my profile,
what do you think, Kaimook?

299
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:37,040
What a gentleman.

300
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:41,560
I think you've watched too many dramas.

301
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:52,520
Wait, Kaimook.

302
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:54,920
You act like a child.

303
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:58,920
- Who are you calling a child?
- You, obviously.

304
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:02,560
Why?

305
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,920
You fell on your own.
I didn't do anything.

306
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,520
Why are you angry at me?

307
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,960
Seriously,

308
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:12,960
what did I ever do to make you dislike me?

309
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,960
Why are you nice one minute
and awful the next?

310
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:20,120
Do I really act like that?

311
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:21,320
Yes.

312
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:24,760
Ever since the first day we met.
We were talking normally about photography

313
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:28,760
and when you found out my name was Kaimook
and those photographs belonged to me,

314
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:30,800
suddenly you snapped at me.

315
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:35,120
Why? Is my name so wrong?

316
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,680
Yeah.

317
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,480
Why couldn't your name be Kaigai,

318
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:43,600
Kaiped, or Kaipalo?

319
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,200
Kaipalo is good.

320
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:50,080
I like it. It's delicious.

321
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:52,400
Are you crazy?

322
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:56,360
Is my name destroying
the ecosystem or something?

323
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:05,800
What does it have to do
with the ecosystem?

324
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,560
Da, Da.

325
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:19,080
Da, are you really going back?

326
00:39:21,360 --> 00:39:23,760
Okay, if you want to leave,
I'll drive you myself.

327
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,600
But you have to stay for dinner first.

328
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:30,000
Dad invited Mr. Narathon over tonight.

329
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:34,960
Mr. Narathon?

330
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,200
Yes.

331
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,960
Since you already know him,

332
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,160
it'd look rude
if you didn't stay for dinner.

333
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:42,760
Can I ask you for that?

334
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,640
Okay, fine.

335
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,640
I'm only doing it for you.

336
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:51,440
Thank you so much.

337
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:56,480
But, Na,

338
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:59,040
if you want me to stay for dinner,

339
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:00,920
there's one thing you have to do for me.

340
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:01,960
Of course.

341
00:40:02,520 --> 00:40:05,640
I'd do anything for you.

342
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:30,280
The project you told me about
sounds very interesting.

343
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:32,920
The one about breeding rare marine fish.

344
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:36,080
Well, let's continue discussing it later.

345
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:39,520
- Sure.
- Where's Na? Why isn't he here with us?

346
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:42,000
He went out to buy something for Da.

347
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:45,240
But he's been gone for a long time now.

348
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,360
What did you ask him to buy, Da?

349
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:50,000
Scallops.

350
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:54,600
There's already loads of seafood
on the table.

351
00:40:54,680 --> 00:40:56,320
That's still not enough?

352
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:59,800
Can you call him and ask where he is?

353
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:04,760
No need to call him.
He's probably driving.

354
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:07,920
I think you should call him.

355
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,800
At least we'll know where he is.

356
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:13,120
Sure.

357
00:41:29,680 --> 00:41:31,040
The time has come.

358
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:35,040
No matter how hard you try to stop it,

359
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:38,600
they are destined to meet.

360
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:45,440
Hello, Na, how's the squid hunt going?

361
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:47,600
You must be hungry already.

362
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:49,800
Of course I am.

363
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:52,520
I'm almost there.

364
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:55,840
Please be patient.

365
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:58,720
And how close is your "almost there"?

366
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:11,080
Hello? Hello, Da?

367
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:13,640
Hello?

368
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,640
A ghost. A ghost!

369
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:24,960
Maybe you imagined it?

370
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:28,280
No, I didn't. I really saw it.

371
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:30,400
You saw a ghost again?

372
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:31,800
Where?

373
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:35,680
In the pool. Mook, it was scary.

374
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:38,240
I think you should calm down.

375
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:40,880
I'm serious, Mr. Thon.

376
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:43,440
I really saw it. It was so scary.

377
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:44,960
It's all slimy and gross too.

378
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,200
What's going on?

379
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:48,560
Na.

380
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,840
I saw a ghost again.

381
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:54,280
A ghost? Again?

382
00:42:57,280 --> 00:42:58,680
It's okay.

383
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:01,480
Da, let's eat.

384
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:54,720
Don't go.

385
00:43:55,320 --> 00:43:57,680
You'll all die.

386
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:07,800
How long have all of you
been living in this house?

387
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,000
Are you alright?

388
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:12,360
Where is my child?!

389
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:16,560
Mr. Phum,

390
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:18,320
did you kill our child?!

391
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:20,640
Why don't you say anything?!

392
00:44:50,800 --> 00:44:52,600
‪Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
